	abstract = {The optimal collimator and energy window for Yttrium-90 bremsstrahlung SPECT imaging was investigated in the study. Yttrium-90 images were acquired with a dual-head gamma camera, equipped with parallel hole collimators and 90Y vial for different energy windows ranging from 56 to 232 keV. Image quality parameters (sensitivity, \%FOV, and S/B) were examined for the energy window and collimator combinations. It is concluded that the optimal SPECT imaging was achieved using FBP Method with a HEGP collimator and the energy window of 90–110 keV.},
